A few weeks ago, the Michelle Obama "Natural Hair" viral topic circulated and as we recall, her stylists said she was natural this whole time but got it straightened regularly. Then the #Sheamoisture controversy happened, and now we came to the question: Is straightening your hair like, Michelle, okay for naturals? Have we truly liberated ourselves from our past ways? Although it was liberating to know that our first black first lady was natural (behind scenes), we can't help but ask "is straightening our natural hair just continuing the issue of beauty and identity for the woman of color in our society?" Ok, we know it is less harmful to flat iron our hair than to perm it, but are we still perpetuating the "my natural hair is unmanageable...it's better straightened" philosophy that has existed throughout our history? Some say that's going too far and straightening is just another hairstyle, like twist outs or braids, and it is not chasing after the perm life. What do you think? Let's have a talk about our crowns...#crowntalk. ⠀

Looking forward to @londonfestivalofarchitecture Pecha Kucha with @astudio_architects and The Carbon Trust. 2nd June, 6pm. 
Tom Watson (Associate Director) will be talking about the works completed at Seventy Wilson during an evening of quick-fire presentations.

Hosted by Astudio as part of the London Festival of Architecture, the evening will include an exhibition as well as presentations and debate between HTS, Astudio Architects, The Carbon Trust and students from Brunel University.

Register for tickets via link on our website.

Address: Tower Building, 11 York Road, London, SE1 7NX

Love it or hate it, @mcdonalds has a place in the burger market. They paved the way for many of the burger operators around now and will probably be here long after many have come and gone. I worked at Maccas as a young buck and learnt some amazing life skills there. Things like, how to make a creamy soda using the vanilla syrup line from the shake machine. I learnt how to make jam doughnuts using cheeseburger buns. -
-
Today in the US marks McDonald's birthday. -
-
As discerning burger lovers do guys and girls still go to McDonald's? What do you get? What is the craziest thing you ever ordered/received from Maccas? -
-
I think McDonald's in Australia is different to other countries. I think it is a better product here than in the USA. @mcdonaldsau -
